# Title: Suspicious File Downloaded From Direct IP Via Certutil.EXE
# Author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2023-02-15
# Level: high
# Description: Detects the execution of certutil with certain flags that allow the utility to download files from direct IPs.
# MITRE Tactic: Command and Control
# Tags: attack.stealth, attack.t1027, attack.command-and-control, attack.t1105
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_certutil_download_direct_ip.yml

CommandLine IN ("*urlcache *", "*verifyctl *", "*URL *") CommandLine IN ("*://1*", "*://2*", "*://3*", "*://4*", "*://5*", "*://6*", "*://7*", "*://8*", "*://9*") Image="*\\certutil.exe" OR OriginalFileName="CertUtil.exe" NOT CommandLine="*://7-*"